:: End of the story {"position":"2400,1400","size":"100,100"}
<div style="font-size: 30px; text-align: center">
Pietro step back into the courtyard, the testiera tucks under one arm and the sella da parata balances against his hip. Straw crackles underfoot. Then a clear blast of the hunting horn cut the morning air, once, twice. The joust will start soon.
He breaks into a run.
At the palazzo steps he catch sight of Annibale II already in the lists’ half-light, pages bustling like swallows. Pietro puts the testiera on the charger’s head, set the plume in the rosette, buckles the cheek plates, and fasten the saddle tight. He checks the resta, offers the lance, and whispers the motto he had learned: Nunc michi.
“Ready, my lord.”
