:: Intro {"position":"875,300","size":"100,100"}
<div style="text-align: center; font-size: 25px">Pietro, a fifteen-year-old squire, entered the service of Signor Annibale II Bentivoglio a month ago, and today his probationary period is coming to an end. How well Pietro performs on the day of the knight tournament will determine whether Signor Bentivoglio keeps Pietro as his squire.
The bells of San Petronio had barely finished their first peal when Pietro headed for the armory of Palazzo Bentivoglio. Annibale II, condottiere, heir to a name that ruled Bologna in living memory, would ride today before the city’s nobles. Jousts were more than sport, they were an important ritual for gaining glory and asserting one's power. Pietro knew it, and so did his lord.

Well, are you ready to help Pietro prove himself a worthy squire so that he can remain in the service of Signor Bentivoglio?  So, let's accompany Pietro to the knight's armoury and help him choose the right equipment for his lord.
